maining in both of macro-and microaggregates followed the order of NPKM {$>$} NPK {$>$} CK for all soil aggregates after the 360-day incubation. Conclusions Our results illustrated that long-term application of manure with mineral fertilizer helps to stabilize or increase the retention of exogenous C in the soil aggregates.},
